edu.mit.csail.db.ml.conf

Class ModelDbConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.mit.csail.db.ml.conf.ModelDbConfig

  • public class ModelDbConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the configuration used to set-up the ModelDB Server. The configuration is specified in a file like in [ModelDB_Dir]/server/src/main/resources/reference.conf. Then, this class can be used to parse the file and read the configuration. This is a SINGLETON class.

      • parse

        public static ModelDbConfig parse(java.lang.String[] args)
                           throws ParseException
        Parse command line arguments and create the singleton ModelDbConfig object.
        Parameters:
        args - - The command line arguments. If the CONF_OPT option is present, then it will be used as the path of the configuration file. Otherwise, the [ModelDB_Dir]/server/src/main/resources/reference.conf will be read.
